<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><procedure xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" appl="X65" id="RPR-000381478" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:procedure.xsd"><title translate="yes">opening rear screen window : reconditioning</title><procprolog translate="no"><status name="" translate="no"/><critdates translate="no"><created date="" translate="no"/><revised modified="" translate="no"/></critdates><procmetadata translate="no"><siename translate="no"/><sieversion translate="no"/><sietype translate="yes">Procedure</sietype><sienumber translate="no"/><domain translate="no"/><company translate="no">RENAULT</company></procmetadata></procprolog><procbody translate="no"><introduction translate="no"><para translate="yes">The screen printed heated grid on the inner face of the window may have an accidental cut, making the affected part of the circuit useless.</para><para translate="yes">The exact point of the cut may be determined using a<?Pub Inc?><materialname otherprops="MAT83_EN" translate="yes" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:materialname.xsd">multimeter</materialname>.</para><para translate="yes">Faults such as these can be repaired by using the repair varnish for the heated rear screen<sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3542379"><linkdesc>vehicle : parts and consumables for the repair</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-002445</linkvalue></sieref>(04B, Consumables - Products).</para></introduction></procbody><procedure id="d1e20" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Determining the exact location of the cut using a voltmeter</title><procbody translate="no"><procsteps translate="no"><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">Switch on the ignition.</para></procstep></procsteps><procsteps translate="no"><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">Switch on the heated rear screen supply.</para></procstep></procsteps></procbody></procedure><procedure id="d1e35" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Detection between lines "B" and "A"</title><procbody translate="no"><procsteps translate="no"><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">Connect the<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">+</value></technicalvalue>wire of the voltmeter to the<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">+</value></technicalvalue>feed terminal of the rear screen.</para></procstep></procsteps><procsteps translate="no"><marklayer id="marklayer-d1e50" translate="no"><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-50X04X12X02-01X22-1-5.1" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">B</designation></mark><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-50X04X12X02-01X22-1-5.2" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">A</designation></mark><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-50X04X12X02-01X22-1-5.3" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">C</designation></mark></marklayer><figure id="50-04-12-02-8-repair-50-04-12-02-01-22-1-5-1" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000006401_LAY-000092669.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/></figure><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">Put the<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">-</value></technicalvalue>wire of the voltmeter on a filament at the<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">-</value></technicalvalue>terminal side of the rear screen (line<markref format="dita" href="#d1e35/50-04-12-02-8-repair-50-04-12-02-01-22-1-5-1" scope="local" translate="no" type="figure">B</markref>): the voltage obtained should be roughly equal to that of the battery.</para></procstep><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">Move the<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">-</value></technicalvalue>wire towards line<markref format="dita" href="#d1e35/50-04-12-02-8-repair-50-04-12-02-01-22-1-5-1" scope="local" translate="no" type="figure">A</markref>(arrowed line): the voltage gradually drops.</para></procstep></procsteps><procsteps translate="no"><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">A sudden voltage drop indicates that the filament is cut at that point.</para><noteR translate="no" type="note"><para translate="yes">Note:</para><para translate="yes">Do this operation for each filament.</para></noteR></procstep></procsteps></procbody></procedure><procedure id="d1e117" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Detection between lines "C" and "A"</title><procbody translate="no"><procsteps translate="no"><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">Connect the<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">-</value></technicalvalue>wire of the voltmeter to the<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">-</value></technicalvalue>terminal of the rear screen.</para></procstep></procsteps><procsteps translate="no"><marklayer id="marklayer-d1e132" translate="no"><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-50X04X12X02-01X22-1-5.4" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">C</designation></mark><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-50X04X12X02-01X22-1-5.5" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">B</designation></mark><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-50X04X12X02-01X22-1-5.6" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">A</designation></mark></marklayer><figure id="50-04-12-02-9-repair-50-04-12-02-01-22-1-5-2" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000006402_LAY-000092670.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/></figure><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">Put the<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">+</value></technicalvalue>wire of the voltmeter on a filament on the<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">+</value></technicalvalue>terminal of the rear screen (line<markref format="dita" href="#d1e117/50-04-12-02-9-repair-50-04-12-02-01-22-1-5-2" scope="local" translate="no" type="figure">C</markref>); the voltage obtained should be roughly equal to that of the battery.</para></procstep><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">Move the<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">+</value></technicalvalue>wire towards line<markref format="dita" href="#d1e117/50-04-12-02-9-repair-50-04-12-02-01-22-1-5-2" scope="local" translate="no" type="figure">A</markref>(arrowed line); the voltage gradually drops.</para></procstep></procsteps><procsteps translate="no"><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">A sudden voltage drop indicates that the filament is cut at that point.</para><noteR translate="no" type="note"><para translate="yes">Note:</para><para translate="yes">Do this operation for each filament.</para></noteR></procstep></procsteps></procbody></procedure><procedure id="d1e194" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Repairing the filament</title><procbody translate="no"><procsteps translate="no"><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">Clean the section to be treated to remove all dust or grease, preferably using alcohol or a glass cleaner.</para></procstep></procsteps><procsteps translate="no"><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">Wipe immediately with a clean and dry cloth.</para></procstep></procsteps><procsteps translate="no"><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">To obtain a regular line during the repair, apply adhesive tape on either side of the section to be repaired, leaving the conducting line free.</para></procstep></procsteps><procsteps translate="no"><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">Before using the varnish, shake the bottle to prevent the silver particles settling at the bottom.</para></procstep></procsteps></procbody></procedure><procedure id="d1e210" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Repair</title><procbody translate="no"><procsteps translate="no"><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">Carry out the repair using a small brush, applying a sufficiently thick layer. In the case of successive layers, observe a drying time between each layer.</para><noteR translate="no" type="note"><para translate="yes">Note:</para><para translate="yes">Do not repeat the operation more than three times.</para></noteR></procstep></procsteps><procsteps translate="no"><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">If the varnish runs however, it can be removed using the point of a knife or a razor blade, but only after several hours, once the product has properly hardened.</para></procstep></procsteps><procsteps translate="no"><figure id="50-04-12-02-10-repair-50-04-12-02-01-22-1-5-3" translate="no"><image dimension="F2 (85x85) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000006407_LAY-000092671.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/></figure><procstep translate="no"><para translate="yes">The adhesive tape used as a guide must not be removed until approximately one hour after application. The tape must be pulled off perpendicularly to the resistance, in the direction of the arrow. When used at an ambient temperature of<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">20ËšC</value></technicalvalue>, the varnish is fully dry in three hours. At lower temperatures, the drying time is slightly longer.</para></procstep></procsteps></procbody></procedure></procedure>